You can trace Macbeth’s character progression through his soliloquies. Across Acts 1 to 4, Macbeth progresses
from being uncertain to decisive, despite having moments of doubt along the way. His soliloquies in Act5 signal
a return to pensiveness as he broods over his unhappy future in Scene 3, and on the futility of life in Scene 5.
